Heap + Queue Approach :

Count task frequencies and push into a max-heap.
At each time unit, pick the most frequent task and execute it.
Decrease its count and push it into a cooldown queue with time + n.
When cooldown expires, push the task back into the heap.
Continue until both heap and queue are empty.

Time Complexity: O(N log 26) ≈ O(N)
Space Complexity: O(26) ≈ O(1)

Solution:
import heapq
from collections import Counter,deque

class Solution:
    def leastInterval(self, tasks: List[str], n: int) -> int:
        count= Counter(tasks)
        maxHeap=[-cnt for cnt in count.values()]
        heapq.heapify(maxHeap)

        time=0
        q=deque() #store pairs of -cnt , time to check when to add task back to the maxHeap

        while maxHeap or q:
            time += 1

            if maxHeap:
                cnt = heapq.heappop(maxHeap)
                cnt+=1
                if cnt:
                    q.append([cnt,time+n])
            if q and q[0][1] == time:
                cnt = q.popleft()[0]
                heapq.heappush(maxHeap, cnt)
        
        return time




